{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "These are the words of King Lemuel, an oracle, taught to him by his mother.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "What shall I tell you, my son?—the son I gave birth to, the son given in response to my vows.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Don't waste your strength sleeping with women, those that bring down kings.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Lemuel, kings shouldn't be drinking wine, rulers shouldn't be drinking alcohol. \n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For if they drink, they'll forget what the law says, and pervert the rights of those who are suffering.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Give alcohol to those who are dying, and wine to those who are in terrible distress.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Let them drink so they can forget their poverty, and not remember their troubles any longer.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Speak up for those who have no voice, for the rights of those marginalized by society.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Speak up and judge fairly; defend the poor and destitute.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who can find a strong, capable wife? She's worth more than jewels! \n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Her husband has complete confidence in her, and with her he'll never be poor.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She brings him good, not evil, all her life.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She gets wool and flax, and with her eager hands turns them into clothes.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Like a merchant's ship, she brings food from far away.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She gets up while it's still dark to make breakfast for her family, and to plan what her servant girls need to do.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She looks at a field, and decides to buy it; from the money she's earned she buys a vineyard.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She's keen to get ready, and works hard with her strong arms.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She knows that the things she makes are valuable. She keeps busy—her lamp burns late into the night.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She spins the thread and weaves the cloth. \n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She's generous to the poor, and gives help to the needy.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She doesn't worry if it snows, because her whole family has warm clothing.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She makes herself bedspreads; she dresses in fine linen and purple clothes.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Her husband is well-respected in the council at the town gates, where he sits with the town elders.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She makes linen clothes for sale, and supplies merchants with belts.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She's clothed with strength and dignity, and she is happy about the future.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She speaks wise words, and she's kind when she gives instructions.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She looks after the needs of her whole household, and she's never idle.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Her children are quick to bless her. Her husband praises her too, saying,\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "{\n"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Many women do great things, but you are better than all of them!",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Charm can deceive, and beauty fades, but a woman who honors the Lord should be praised.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "31",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Give her the recognition she deserves; praise her publicly for what she's done.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}